President Trump made remarks at the North DFAC (Dining Facility) at Bagram Airfield in Afghanistan. He expressed his gratitude to the military and mentioned Senator Barrasso's support. Trump highlighted the $2.5 trillion spent on rebuilding the military and praised its current state, emphasizing that it is no longer depleted. He mentioned having lunch with the troops and expressed his appreciation for their work. The President also joked about the length of the flight to Afghanistan.